Household expenditures with Malaria¶

This Python notebook will calculate expenditures with Malaria at household level, with data collected by a field research conducted in the Brazilian Amazon region in April 2022.

Pre-processing¶

All the data pre-processing will be conducted in this section. First, the necessary Python libraries will be imported. Then, all the datasets are loaded into Python and treatment ensues.

Libraries¶

'Pandas' will be used to create dataframe objects. 'OS' will be used to better interface with the operational system and read environment variables. 'dotenv' is used to access said variables. 'Numpy', 'math' and 'scipy' will be used to provide necessary math operations. 'Datetime' allows operations with dates. 'Random' generates pseudo-random numbers. 'tqdm', 'stasmodels' and 'sklearn' estimate OLS models. Finally, 'IPython', 'seaborn' and 'matplotlib' are graphical interfaces, while 'warnings' is used to suppress warnings.

Dataset treatment¶

Here, the datasets will be treated as needed. Regarding the main one, 'df', deleting the unwanted columns is the first step.

In [856]:
df.drop(columns = ['comodos', 'banheiros', 'som', 'tv', 'dvd', 'geladeira','freezer','automovel',
          'computador', 'fogao', 'microondas', 'motocicleta', 'celular', 'relacao_responsavel','situ_domicilio',

         'auxilio_emergencial', 'outro_auxilio', 'n_sabe_auxilio', 'alfabetizacao', 'escol_respond',
         'trabalho', 'tipo_trabalho','casos_malaria', 'multiplos_beneficios', 'configuracao_familiar', 'trabalho', 'tipo_trabalho','outro_medicamento_receita','tipo_mosquiteiro'], inplace = True)

The households that didn't register malaria episodes between Jan 2019-Mar 2022 (date groups 1 and 2) should be deleted as well.

In [857]:
df.drop(df[(df.grupo_data != 1)&(df.grupo_data != 2)].index, inplace = True)

The resulting dataframe has 1131 rows (each one corresponding to a distinct household) and 101 columns.

In [858]:
df.shape
Out[858]:
(1131, 105)

When the respondent didn't remember the month/day of the latest malaria episode, the median value was assigned. A week of the month of the latest malaria episode was created. Also, a column with the age group of the patient of the latest malaria episode was created.

In [859]:
df['mes_malaria'].replace(0, np.nan, inplace = True)
df['dia_malaria'].replace(0, np.nan, inplace = True)

df['semana_mes_malaria'] = 0
df['faixa_etaria'] = 0

for i in range(len(df)):
    if pd.isna(df.loc[df.index[i],'mes_malaria']) or df.loc[df.index[i],'mes_malaria'] == 0:
        median_value = np.nanmedian(df['mes_malaria'])
        df.loc[df.index[i],'mes_malaria'] = median_value
       
    if pd.isna(df.loc[df.index[i],'dia_malaria']) or df.loc[df.index[i],'dia_malaria'] == 0:
        median_value = np.nanmedian(df['dia_malaria'])
        df.loc[df.index[i],'dia_malaria'] = median_value
    
    if df.loc[df.index[i],'dia_malaria'] in range(1,7):
        df.loc[df.index[i],'semana_mes_malaria'] = 1
    elif df.loc[df.index[i],'dia_malaria'] in range(8,14):
        df.loc[df.index[i],'semana_mes_malaria'] = 2
    elif df.loc[df.index[i],'dia_malaria'] in range(15,21):
        df.loc[df.index[i],'semana_mes_malaria'] = 3
    else:
        df.loc[df.index[i],'semana_mes_malaria'] = 4

    if df.loc[df.index[i], 'idade'] < 18:
        df.loc[df.index[i], 'faixa_etaria'] = 1
    elif df.loc[df.index[i], 'idade'] >= 60:
        df.loc[df.index[i], 'faixa_etaria'] = 2
    else:
        df.loc[df.index[i], 'faixa_etaria'] = 3
        
colunas = ['uf', 'zona', 'sexo','ano_malaria','mes_malaria','dia_malaria','semana_mes_malaria','faixa_etaria','exame_tratamento', 'internacao', 'acompanhante_internacao', 'meio_transporte_postinho', 'meio_transporte_ubs', 'meio_transporte_upa', 'meio_transporte_hospital_particular', 'meio_transporte_clinica_particular', 'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao', 'trabalho_mal', 'tipo_trabalho_mal', 'pecuaria_mal', 'tipo_pecuaria', 'agricultura_mal', 'tipo_agricultura', 'pesca_mal', 'tipo_pesca', 'garimpo_mal', 'tipo_garimpo', 'comercio_mal', 'tipo_comercio', 'extrat_mal', 'tipo_extrat', 'casa_mal', 'faculdade_mal', 'substituto_trab_mal', 'pgto_pecuaria_mal', 'pgto_agricultura_mal', 'pgto_pesca_mal', 'pgto_garimpo_mal', 'pgto_comercio_mal', 'pgto_extrat_mal', 'pgto_casa_mal', 'escolaridade', 'exame', 'pgto_exame']
for coluna in colunas:
    df[coluna] = df[coluna].astype(str).apply(lambda x: x.replace('.0',''))
df.head()

Household Expenditures¶

In the following sections, the household expenditures in both Direct and Indirect modalities will be estimated.

Direct Expenditures¶

The Direct Expenditures are:

  • Prevention;
  • Medical,
  • Non-Medical.

Prevention¶

The prevention expenditures will be estimated employing data from the Family Budget Survey. Stratified by State, the annual familiar expenditures with repelents, insecticides, bed nets and such is informed by POF, in 2022 prices. So, for every household that informed the private acquisition of one of those items, the full yearly expenditure, acording to the household State of residence, was accrued.

In [867]:
df['prevention_expenditures'] = 0

for i in df.index:
    if ((df.at[i, 'cortinado'] != 1) or (df.at[i, 'cortinado'] != 2) or (((df.at[i, 'cortinado'] == 1) or (df.at[i, 'cortinado'] == 2)) and (df.at[i ,'mosquiteiro'] != 2))) and ((df.at[i, 'prevencao_malaria'] != 1) or ((df.at[i, 'prevencao_malaria'] == 1) and (df.loc[i, 'obtencao_remedio'] != 2))) and ((df.at[i, 'repelente'] != 1) or ((df.at[i, 'repelente'] == 1) and (df.at[i, 'obtencao_repelente'] != 2))) and ((df.at[i, 'inseticida'] != 1) or ((df.at[i, 'inseticida'] == 1) and (df.at[i, 'obtencao_inseticida'] != 2))):
        continue
    else:
        uf = df.at[i, 'uf']
        moradores = df.at[i, 'num_moradores']
        gasto = df_prevention.query(f"UF == '{uf}'")['media'].squeeze()

        if(((df.at[i, 'cortinado'] == 1) or (df.at[i, 'cortinado'] == 2)) and df.at[i ,'mosquiteiro'] == 2) or (df.at[i, 'repelente'] == 1 and df.at[i, 'obtencao_repelente'] == 2) or (df.at[i, 'inseticida'] == 1 and df.at[i, 'obtencao_inseticida'] == 2):
           df.at[i,'prevention_expenditures'] = moradores*gasto

df.drop(['num_moradores','cortinado', 'mosquiteiro', 'prevencao_malaria', 'obtencao_remedio','repelente', 'obtencao_repelente', 'inseticida', 'obtencao_inseticida'], axis = 1, inplace = True)

Medical¶

The Medical Direct Expenditures are:

  • Exams;
  • Doctor appointments/ambulatorial care;
  • Medicines,
  • Hospitalizations.
Exams¶

The exam expenditures are simply derived from the unitary exam price.

These cost components will be estimated by a similar mean as done in regard to Prevention Direct Expenditures, employing the Family Budget Survey data, also in 2022 prices. All the occurrences of tradional/faith healers were free of charge, so those were disregarded.

Hospitalization¶

Hospitalization costs are divided into hospital expenditures and other medicines.

Hospital¶

Only one family reported paying hospitalization costs out-of-pocket, with a nominal expenditure of BRL 100, an obviously unrealistic value. Being that, household expenditures on hospitalization will be disregarded.

In [877]:
df.drop(columns = ['pgto_internacao', 'valor_internacao'], inplace = True)

Once again, one family didn't remember how much was spent on medicines demanded by hospitalization. The same procedure as above was applied.

Non-Medical¶

The Non-Medical expenditures are:

  • Transportation:
    • Patient,
    • Caregiver.
  • Food (caregiver),
  • Lodging (caregiver).
Transportation¶

All transportation costs are considered as being incurred in roundtrips, i.e. will be multiplied by two. Eight possible transportation methods were considered into the survey:

  • By foot;
  • Own vehicle;
  • Boat;
  • Uber/transport apps;
  • Bus;
  • Cab,
  • Lift.
  • SUS car.

The same methodology will be employed, irrespective of being patient or caregiver.

Own vehicle¶

The expenditures incurred by transportation in a household-owned vehicle will be calculated by constructing a hypothetical vehicle through a weighted-average of the fuel consumption (in L/km) of the enry-level models of the annual top 10 best-selling vehicles in the Brazilian market, compiled by FENABRAVE ( Federao Nacional da Distribuio de Veculos Automotore - National Federation of the Distribution of Automobile Vehicles) and Inmentro, in the National Labelling Programme. The average fuel price to final consumer is a time series compiled by ANP (Agncia Nacional de Petrleo - National Petroleum Agency), by month/year. The average speed of the vehicle is assumed to be 60 km/h. So, the expenditure for a single round of the trip is given by the following equation:

expenditure = time spent in transportation by car while seeking care
 X average speed of a car (60 km/h)
 X fuel consumption of the hypothetical vehicle constructed for the year of the latest malaria episodia
 X average fuel price to the final consumer in the month/year of the latest episode, in the State of residency of the patient )

In [882]:
def custo_direto_veiculo_proprio(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_veiculos, df_gasolina):
    consumo = df_veiculos.query(f"ano == '{ano}'")['consumo'].squeeze()
    preco_gasolina = df_gasolina.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & mes == '{mes}' & uf == '{uf}'")['preco'].squeeze()
    qtd_gasolina = distancia/consumo
    return qtd_gasolina*preco_gasolina
Boat¶

In a similar approach as done above, a hypothetical boat was constructed. This time, it was a 2-time gasoline 15HP Yamaha engine, which, according to Fonseca e Souza (2017) e Chantey (2012), is the most common boat type in the Amazon region. The specific fuel consumption data (in L/h) was found in the 2012 US National Boat Survey. The fuel data is the same as above. So, the expenditure for a single round of the trip is:

expenditure = time spent in transportation by boat while seeking care
 X average fuel consumption of a hypothetical boat
 X average fuel price to the final consumer in the month/year of the latest episode, in the State of residency of the patient

In [883]:
boat_consumption = float(os.environ["AVERAGE_BOAT_FUEL_CONSUMPTION"])
In [884]:
def custo_direto_barco(ano, mes, uf, tempo, consumo_barco, df_gasolina):
    preco_gasolina = df_gasolina.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & mes == '{mes}' & uf == '{uf}'")['preco'].squeeze()
    return consumo_barco*preco_gasolina*tempo
Bus¶

Bus expenditures were calculated by amassing a time series of the bus fares in the capital cities of the States in the Amazon region, available at their official channels of communication and news websites. If the patient was a minor, two fares were deemed necessary, otherwise only one. The formula is:

expenditure = bus fare at the month/year of the latest episode of malaria
 X number of travellers

In [885]:
def custo_direto_onibus(ano, mes, uf, faixa_etaria, df_onibus):
    return df_onibus.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & mes == '{mes}' & uf == '{uf}'")['tarifa'].squeeze() if faixa_etaria != 1 else 2*df_onibus.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & mes == '{mes}' & uf == '{uf}'")['tarifa'].squeeze()
Cab¶

Cab expenditures were calculated by establishing a time series of cab fares, similar to the process adopted in the bus estimation. The main caveat here is that the total expenditure is comprised of a fixed part, corresponding to the start of race fare, and a variable one, dependent on the length othe travel. We assumed a speed of 60 km/h. So, the formula is as it follows:

expenditure = fixed fare +
 kilometer fare
 X average speed (60 km/h)
 X time spent seeking care

In [886]:
def custo_direto_taxi(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_taxi):
    bandeirada = df_taxi.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & mes == '{mes}' & uf == '{uf}'")['bandeirada'].squeeze()
    km = df_taxi.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & mes == '{mes}' & uf == '{uf}'")['km'].squeeze()
    return bandeirada + km*distancia
Uber¶

To estimate the Uber fare, a Uber fare function was computed regressing the fare of 200k Uber travels around the world into several variables, as described below.

Uber fare function

    vif = pd.DataFrame()

    vif['Features'] = X.columns
    vif['VIF'] = [variance_inflation_factor(X.values, i) for i in range(X.shape[1])]

In [904]:



     


Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix = pd.DataFrame(np.zeros([5,8]), columns=['Train-R2','Test-R2','Train-RSS','Test-RSS',
                                                                            'Train-MSE','Test-MSE','Train-RMSE','Test-RMSE'])
rc=np.random.choice(treino_X_std.loc[:,treino_X_std.nunique()>50].columns,3)
def avalia_modelo(n, prev1,prev2):
    plt.figure(figsize=[15,6])
    for e,i in enumerate(rc):
        plt.subplot(2,3,e+1)
        plt.scatter(y=treino_y, x=treino_X_std[i], label='Real')
        plt.scatter(y=prev1, x=treino_X_std[i], label='Previsto')
        plt.legend()
    plt.show()

    print('\n\n{}Training Set Metrics{}'.format('-'*20, '-'*20))
    print('\nTraining Set R2 --->',round(r2_score(treino_y, prev1),20))
    print('Training Set RSS --->',round(np.sum(np.square(treino_y-prev1)),20))
    print('Training Set MSE --->',round(mean_squared_error(treino_y, prev1),20))
    print('Training Set RMSE --->',round(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(treino_y, prev1)),20))

    print('\n{}Test Set Metrics{}'.format('-'*20, '-'*20))
    print('\nTest Set R2 --->',round(r2_score(teste_y, prev2),20))
    print('Test Set RSS --->',round(np.sum(np.square(teste_y-prev2)),20))
    print('Test Set MSE --->',round(mean_squared_error(teste_y, prev2),20))
    print('Test Set RMSE --->',round(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(teste_y, prev2)),20))
    print('\n{}Residuals Plotting{}'.format('-'*20, '-'*20))
    
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Train-R2']  = round(r2_score(treino_y, prev1),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Test-R2']   = round(r2_score(teste_y, prev2),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Train-RSS'] = round(np.sum(np.square(treino_y-prev1)),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Test-RSS']  = round(np.sum(np.square(teste_y-prev2)),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Train-MSE'] = round(mean_squared_error(treino_y, prev1),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Test-MSE']  = round(mean_squared_error(teste_y, prev2),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Train-RMSE']= round(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(treino_y, prev1)),20)
    Model_Evaluation_Comparison_Matrix.loc[n,'Test-RMSE'] = round(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(teste_y, prev2)),20)

    plt.figure(figsize=[15,4])

    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    sns.distplot((treino_y - prev1))
    plt.title('Error Terms')          
    plt.xlabel('Errors')
    plt.ylabel('Density')

    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    plt.scatter(treino_y,prev1)
    plt.plot([treino_y.min(),treino_y.max()],[treino_y.min(),treino_y.max()], 'r--')
    plt.title('Test vs Predict')         
    plt.xlabel('Y-Test')                       
    plt.ylabel('Y-Predict')                       
    plt.show()

Uber fare estimation


To estimate the fare, a travel was considered of medium length if it lasted between 20 and 40 minutes. If the patient was a minor, two travelers were considere, if else, only one. All travels were considered to be done in daytime and a random binary was assigned to determine if the call for a trip was put between the 10th and 20th minute of the hour.











In [906]:



     


def custo_direto_uber(ano, mes, dia, semana_mes, distancia, faixa_etaria, API):
    dia_semana = dt.datetime(int(ano),int(mes), int(dia)).weekday()
    if dia_semana == 6:
        dia_semana_1 = 1
        dia_semana_2 = 0
        dia_semana_3 = 0
    elif dia_semana == 0:
        dia_semana_1 = 0
        dia_semana_2 = 1
        dia_semana_3 = 0
    elif dia_semana == 1:
        dia_semana_1 = 0
        dia_semana_2 = 0
        dia_semana_3 = 1
    else:
        dia_semana_1 = 0
        dia_semana_2 = 0
        dia_semana_3 = 0
    
    if mes == 2:
        mes_02 = 1
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 0
    elif mes == 6:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 1
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 0
    elif mes == 7:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 1
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 0
    elif mes == 8:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 1
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 0
    elif mes == 10:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 1
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 0
    elif mes == 11:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 1
        mes_12 = 0
    elif mes == 12:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 1
    else:
        mes_02 = 0
        mes_06 = 0
        mes_07 = 0
        mes_08 = 0
        mes_10 = 0
        mes_11 = 0
        mes_12 = 0
    
    if semana_mes == 1:
        semana_mes_1 = 1
    else:
        semana_mes_1 = 0
    
    if tempo > 20 and tempo <=40:
        viagem_media = 1
    else:
        viagem_media = 0
    
    if faixa_etaria == 1:
        passageiros_2 = 1
        passageiros_3 = 0
        passageiros_4 = 0
    else:
        passageiros_2 = 0
        passageiros_3 = 0
        passageiros_4 = 0
    
    decil_hora_2 = random.choice([0,1])
    dist = distancia
    ano = int(ano)
    noite = 0
    
    data = pd.DataFrame({'dist': dist,
                        'ano': ano,
                        'mes_02': mes_02,
                        'mes_06': mes_06,
                        'mes_07': mes_07,
                        'mes_08': mes_08,
                        'mes_10': mes_10,
                        'mes_11': mes_11,
                        'mes_12': mes_12,
                        'viagem_media': viagem_media,
                        'semana_mes_1': semana_mes_1,
                        'noite': noite,
                        'passageiros_2': passageiros_2,
                        'passageiros_3': passageiros_3,
                        'passageiros_4': passageiros_4,
                        'dia_semana_1': dia_semana_1,
                        'dia_semana_2': dia_semana_2,
                        'dia_semana_3': dia_semana_3,
                        'decil_hora_2': decil_hora_2},
                       index =[0])
    return API.predict(data).squeeze() if API.predict(data).squeeze() > 7 else 7



     















Lift¶
Same costs as own vehicle.











By foot and SUS car¶
These two means of transportation were considered to have only indirect costs associated.











Food and lodging (caregiver)¶
The expenditures associated with those two items were considered as a daily fraction of the monthly minimum wage per year, in 2019 prices. The formula is:


expenditure = (days of hospitalization/30 days in a month)

 X monthly minnimum wage











In [907]:



     


def custo_hospedagem_alimentacao(ano, dias, df_salario):
    salario = df_salario.query(f"ano == '{ano}'")['salario_minimo'].squeeze()
    proporcao_internacao = dias/30
    return proporcao_internacao*salario

Indirect expenditures¶
The Indirect expenditures considered are:


    

  • Opportunity cost (time spent seeking care);
    • 

  • Absenteeism from work (patient):
      

    • Main activity,
      • 

    • Other productive activities.
      • 

    

    • 

  • Absenteeism from school (patient),
    • 

  • Absenteeism from work (caregiver).
    • 












Opportunity cost (time spent seeking care)/absenteeism from school and main work activity¶
The opportunity cost/absenteeism is evaluated differently for adult and minor patients.











Minor patients¶
For minor patients, the hourly wage is evaluated as the hourly transfer from the Federal Government through FUNDEB (Fundo de Desenvolvimento da Educao Bsica - Fund for the Development of Basic Education), according to year, State, zone of living (rural/urban) and level of education.











Adult patients¶
For adults, the hourly wage is evaluated as the hourly average salary, by year and State, derived from data of the first visit (5th in pandemic years: 2020/21) PNAD Contnua (Pesquisa Nacional por Amostragem de Domcilios - Continuous National Survey by Household Sampling), deflated to 2019 prices.











Opportunity cost estimation¶
Now it's possible to establish an opportunity cost function.











In [910]:



     


def custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb):
    if faixa_etaria == '1':
        if idade <= 3:
            valor_menor = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['creche'].squeeze()
        elif idade >= 4 and idade <= 5:
            valor_menor = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['pre_escola'].squeeze()
        elif idade >= 6 and idade <=10:
            valor_menor = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['fundamental_I'].squeeze()
        elif idade >= 11 and idade <=14:
            valor_menor = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['fundamental_II'].squeeze()
        else:
            valor_menor = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['medio'].squeeze()

        valor_acompanhante = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
        valor = valor_menor + valor_acompanhante
    else:
        valor = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
    return valor*tempo



     















With the above definitions, it is now possible to estimate the direct and indirect expenditures with transportation.

In [912]:



     


for i in df.index:
    if df.at[i,'exame_tratamento'] == '1':
        for coluna_meio, coluna_tempo in zip(df[colunas_meio], df[colunas_tempo]):
            if pd.isna(df.at[i,coluna_meio]):
                continue
            else:
                ano = df.at[i,'ano_malaria']
                mes = df.at[i,'mes_malaria']
                dia = df.at[i,'dia_malaria']
                semana_mes = df.at[i,'semana_mes_malaria']
                uf = df.at[i,'uf']
                zona = df.at[i,'zona']
                sexo = df.at[i,'sexo']
                faixa_etaria = df.at[i,'faixa_etaria']
                idade = df.at[i,'idade']
                distancia = df.at[i, coluna_tempo]
                tempo = df.at[i, coluna_tempo]/60
                nucleo = coluna_meio[4:]
                
                if df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '1':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_a_pe'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_a_pe'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = np.nan
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                
                if df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '2':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_onibus'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_onibus'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_onibus(ano, mes, uf, faixa_etaria, df_bus)
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

                elif df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '3':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_veiculo_proprio'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_veiculo_proprio'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_veiculo_proprio(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_vehicle, df_gasoline)
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

                elif df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '4':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_carona'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_carona'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_veiculo_proprio(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_vehicle, df_gasoline)
                    custo_oportunidade_passageiro = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                    faixa_etaria_caroneiro = random.choice(['2','3'])
                    if faixa_etaria_caroneiro == '2':
                        idade_caroneiro = 37.5
                    else:
                         idade_caroneiro = 67.5
                    sexo_caroneiro = random.choice(['1','2'])
                    custo_oportunidade_caroneiro = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade_caroneiro, faixa_etaria_caroneiro, tempo, sexo_caroneiro, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade_passageiro + custo_oportunidade_caroneiro
                        
                elif df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '5':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_taxi'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_taxi'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_taxi(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_cab)
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                
                elif df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '6':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_uber'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_uber'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_uber(ano, mes, dia, semana_mes, distancia, faixa_etaria, API)
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                
                elif df.at[i,coluna_meio] == '7':
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_barco'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_barco'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_barco(ano, mes, uf, tempo, boat_consumption, df_gasoline)
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                
                else:
                    coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_sus'
                    coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_sus'
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = np.nan
                    df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
    else:
        continue

for i in df.index:
    if df.at[i,'internacao'] == '1' and df.at[i, 'acompanhante_internacao'] == '1':
        if pd.isna(df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao']):
            continue
        else:
            ano = df.at[i,'ano_malaria']
            mes = df.at[i,'mes_malaria']
            dia = df.at[i,'dia_malaria']
            semana_mes = df.at[i,'semana_mes_malaria']
            uf = df.at[i,'uf']
            zona = df.at[i,'zona']
            sexo = df.at[i,'sexo']
            faixa_etaria = df.at[i,'faixa_etaria']
            idade = df.at[i,'idade']
            if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'tempo_transporte_acompanhante_internacao']):
                distancia = np.nanmedian(df['tempo_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'])
            else:
                distancia = df.at[i, 'tempo_transporte_acompanhante_internacao']
            tempo = df.at[i, 'tempo_transporte_acompanhante_internacao']/60
            nucleo = '_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'

            if df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'] == '1':
                coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_a_pe'
                coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_a_pe'
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = np.nan
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

            if df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'] == '2':
                coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_onibus'
                coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_onibus'
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_onibus(ano, mes, uf, faixa_etaria, df_bus)
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

            elif df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'] == '3':
                coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_veiculo_proprio'
                coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_veiculo_proprio'
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_veiculo_proprio(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_vehicle, df_gasoline)
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

            elif df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'] == '4':
                coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_carona'
                coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_carona'
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_direto] = custo_direto_veiculo_proprio(ano, mes, uf, distancia, df_vehicle, df_gasoline)
                custo_oportunidade_passageiro = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                faixa_etaria_caroneiro = random.choice(['2','3'])
                if faixa_etaria_caroneiro == '2':
                    idade_caroneiro = 37.5
                else:
                     idade_caroneiro = 67.5

                custo_oportunidade_caroneiro = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade_caroneiro, faixa_etaria_caroneiro, tempo, sexo_caroneiro, df_pnad, df_fundeb)
                df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade_passageiro + custo_oportunidade_caroneiro

            elif df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'] == '5':

                coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_taxi'

                df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

            elif df.at[i,'meio_transporte_acompanhante_internacao'] == '6':
                coluna_custo_direto = 'custo_direto' + nucleo + '_uber'
                coluna_custo_indireto = 'custo_indireto' + nucleo + '_uber'

                df.at[i,coluna_custo_indireto] = custo_oportunidade(ano, uf, zona, idade, faixa_etaria, tempo, sexo, df_pnad, df_fundeb)

Absenteeism¶
The following subsections will estimate the expenditures associated with absenteeism, of adult/minor patients and caregivers. Also distinctions between main and other activities will be made.











Patients¶
In this subsection, we will evaluate expenditures associated with absenteeism of patients.











Main work¶
For patients above the legal working age of 14, work absenteeism expenditure was calculated through the formula:


expenditures = days of work lost

 X hours of work lost per day

 X hourly wage


With hourly wage coming from PNAD, in case of paid work, or from POF, in case of self-consumption work. In case of both systems co-existing, half of remuneration was deemed from a paid wage and half of self-consumption. If the hiring of a substitute was deemed necessary, the value was doubled.











In [931]:



     


df['absenteeism_main_work_expenditures'] = 0
for i in df.index:
    if (df.at[i,'idade'] < 14) or ((df.at[i, 'trabalho_mal'] == '2') or (df.at[i, 'trabalho_mal'] == '3')):
        continue
    else:
        ano = df.at[i, 'ano_malaria']
        uf = df.at[i, 'uf']
        sexo = df.at[i, 'sexo']
        zona = df.at[i, 'zona']
        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'dias_trabalho_mal']):
            dias_trabalho = np.nanmedian(df['dias_trabalho_mal'][(df.idade >= 14)&(df.trabalho_mal != '3')])
        else:
            dias_trabalho = df.at[i, 'dias_trabalho_mal']
        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'horas_trabalho_mal']):
            horas_trabalho = np.nanmedian(df['horas_trabalho_mal'][(df.idade >= 14)&(df.trabalho_mal != '3')])
        else:
            horas_trabalho = df.at[i, 'horas_trabalho_mal']
        if df.at[i, 'tipo_trabalho_mal'] == '1':
            remuneracao = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
        elif df.at[i, 'tipo_trabalho_mal'] == '2':
            remuneracao = df_self.query(f"uf == '{uf}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
        else:
            remuneracao_sal = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
            remuneracao_self = df_self.query(f"uf == '{uf}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
            remuneracao = 0.5*(remuneracao_sal+remuneracao_self)
        if df.at[i, 'substituto_trab_mal'] == '1':
            remuneracao *= 2
        df.at[i, 'absenteeism_main_work_expenditures'] = remuneracao*horas_trabalho*dias_trabalho

df.drop(['trabalho_mal', 'dias_trabalho_mal', 'horas_trabalho_mal', 'tipo_trabalho_mal', 'substituto_trab_mal'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
df.head()

School absenteeism (basic education)¶
For minor patients, school absenteeism expenditure was calculate through the formula:


expenditures = days of school lost

 X daily FUNDEB transfer











As a first step, the FUNDEB data has to be reconstructed to a daily expenditure, adopting a 4-hour turn to basic education and a 5-hour turn for high school.











In [933]:



     


df_fundeb[['creche','pre_escola','fundamental_I','fundamental_II']] = 4*df_fundeb[['creche','pre_escola','fundamental_I','fundamental_II']]
df_fundeb['medio'] = 5*df_fundeb['medio']
df_fundeb.head()

In [934]:



     


df['absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures'] = 0
for i in df.index:
    if ((df.at[i,'faixa_etaria'] == '2' or df.at[i,'faixa_etaria'] == '3') and ((df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '8' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '9' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '10') or (df.at[i, 'faculdade_mal'] == '2' or df.at[i, 'faculdade_mal'] == '3'))) or ((df.at[i,'faixa_etaria'] == '1') and (df.at[i, 'faculdade_mal'] == '2' or df.at[i, 'faculdade_mal'] == '3')):
        continue
    else:
        uf = df.at[i,'uf']
        ano = df.at[i,'ano_malaria']
        idade = df.at[i,'idade']
        zona = df.at[i,'zona']
        if idade <= 3:
            escola_dia = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['creche'].squeeze()
        elif idade >= 4 and idade <= 5:
            escola_dia = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['pre_escola'].squeeze()
        elif idade >= 6 and idade <=10:
            escola_dia = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['fundamental_I'].squeeze()
        elif idade >= 11 and idade <=14:
            escola_dia = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['fundamental_II'].squeeze()
        else:
            escola_dia = df_fundeb.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & zona == '{zona}' & uf == '{uf}'")['medio'].squeeze()

        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'dias_faculdade']):
            dias_escola = np.nanmedian(df['dias_faculdade'][((df.faixa_etaria == '1')&(df.faculdade_mal == '1'))|(((df.faixa_etaria == '2')|(df.faixa_etaria == '3'))&(df.faculdade_mal == '1')&((df.escolaridade == '1')|(df.escolaridade == '2')|(df.escolaridade == '3')|(df.escolaridade == '4')|(df.escolaridade == '5')|(df.escolaridade == '6')|(df.escolaridade == '7')))])
        else:
            dias_escola = df.at[i, 'dias_faculdade']
        
        df.at[i, 'absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures'] = escola_dia*dias_escola

df.head()

School absenteeism (tertiary education)¶
Tertiary school absenteeism expenditure was calculate through the formula:


expenditures = days of education lost

 X daily expenditure on a tertiary student


Daily expenditure on a tertiary student was estimated by a weighted average (with weights being the annual total enrollments in private and public systems, obtained from the Superior Schooling Census, of the Brazilian Ministry of Education), the average cost of private schooling, from the Brazilian Map of Superior Education and the average public spenditure on tertiary students, from OECD estimates.


With hourly wage coming from PNAD, in case of paid work, or from POF, in case of self-consumption work.











In [936]:



     


df['absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures'] = 0
for i in df.index:
    if (df.at[i,'idade'] < 18) or ((df.at[i,'faixa_etaria'] == '2' or df.at[i,'faixa_etaria'] == '3') and ((df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '1' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '2' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '3' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '4' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '5' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '6' or df.at[i, 'escolaridade'] == '7') or (df.at[i, 'faculdade_mal'] == '2' or df.at[i, 'faculdade_mal'] == '3'))):
        continue
    else:
        ano = df.at[i,'ano_malaria']
        escola_dia = df_tertiary.query(f"ano == '{ano}'")['custo_total_dia_2019'].squeeze()
        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'dias_faculdade']):
            dias_escola = np.nanmedian(df['dias_faculdade'][(df.faixa_etaria != '1')&(df.faculdade_mal == '1')&((df.escolaridade == '8')|(df.escolaridade == '9')|(df.escolaridade == '10'))])
        else:
            dias_escola = df.at[i, 'dias_faculdade']
        df.at[i, 'absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures'] = escola_dia*dias_escola
df.drop(['dias_faculdade', 'horas_faculdade', 'faculdade_mal', 'escolaridade'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
df.head()

df[['absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures',
   'absenteeism_husbandry_expenditures',
   'absenteeism_fishing_expenditures',

novas_colunas = ['absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures', 'absenteeism_husbandry_expenditures', 'absenteeism_fishing_expenditures', 'absenteeism_extractivism_expenditures', 'absenteeism_mining_expenditures', 'absenteeism_commerce_expenditures']
colunas_realiza = ['agricultura_mal', 'pecuaria_mal', 'pesca_mal', 'extrat_mal', 'garimpo_mal', 'comercio_mal']
colunas_tipo = ['tipo_agricultura', 'tipo_pecuaria', 'tipo_pesca', 'tipo_extrat', 'tipo_garimpo', 'tipo_comercio']
colunas_dias = ['dias_agricultura', 'dias_pecuaria', 'dias_pesca', 'dias_extrat', 'dias_garimpo', 'dias_comercio']
colunas_horas = ['horas_agricultura', 'horas_pecuaria', 'horas_pesca', 'horas_extrat', 'horas_garimpo', 'horas_comercio']
colunas_pgto = ['pgto_agricultura_mal', 'pgto_pecuaria_mal', 'pgto_pesca_mal', 'pgto_extrat_mal', 'pgto_garimpo_mal', 'pgto_comercio_mal']



     















In [939]:



     


for i in df.index:
    for nova_coluna, coluna_realiza, coluna_tipo, coluna_dias, coluna_horas, coluna_pgto in zip(df[novas_colunas], df[colunas_realiza], df[colunas_tipo], df[colunas_dias], df[colunas_horas], df[colunas_pgto]):
        if df.at[i, coluna_realiza] == '2' or df.at[i, coluna_realiza] == '3':
            continue
        else:
            ano = df.at[i, 'ano_malaria']
            uf = df.at[i, 'uf']
            sexo = df.at[i, 'sexo']
            zona = df.at[i, 'zona']
            if pd.isna(df.at[i, coluna_dias]):
                dias = np.nanmedian(df[coluna_dias][df[coluna_realiza] == '1'])
            else:
                dias = df.at[i, coluna_dias]
            if pd.isna(df.at[i, coluna_horas]):
                horas = np.nanmedian(df[coluna_horas][df[coluna_realiza] == '1'])
            else:
                horas = df.at[i, coluna_horas]

            if df.at[i, coluna_tipo] == '1':
                remuneracao = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
            elif df.at[i, coluna_tipo] == '2':
                remuneracao = df_self.query(f"uf == '{uf}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
            else:
                remuneracao_sal = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
                remuneracao_self = df_self.query(f"uf == '{uf}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
                remuneracao = 0.5*(remuneracao_sal+remuneracao_self)
            if df.at[i, coluna_pgto] == '1':
                remuneracao *= 2
            df.at[i, nova_coluna] = remuneracao*horas*dias
                



     















In [940]:



     


df['absenteeism_housework_expenditures'] = 0
for i in df.index:
    if df.at[i, 'casa_mal'] == '2' or df.at[i, 'casa_mal'] == '3':
        continue
    else:
        ano = df.at[i, 'ano_malaria']
        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'dias_casa']):
            dias = np.nanmedian(df['dias_casa'][df.casa_mal == '1'])
        else:
            dias = df.at[i, 'dias_casa']
        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'horas_casa']):
            horas = np.nanmedian(df['horas_casa'][df.casa_mal == '1'])
        else:
            horas = df.at[i, 'horas_casa']
        if df.at[i, 'pgto_casa_mal'] == '1':
            remuneracao = df_minimum.query(f"ano == '{ano}'")['salario_minimo'].squeeze()
            remuneracao = remuneracao/220
            df.at[i, 'absenteeism_housework_expenditures'] = remuneracao*horas*dias

Caregivers¶
The absenteeism expednitures associated with caregivers are defined as:


expenditures = days of work lost

 X 8 daily hours of work lost per day (daily shift)

 X hourly wage


With hourly wage coming from PNAD. A random sex was ascribed to the caregiver.











In [949]:



     


df['absenteeism_caregiver_expenditures'] = 0

for i in df.index:
    if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'internacao']) or (df.at[i, 'internacao'] == 0) or ((df.at[i,'internacao'] == 1) and (df.at[i,'acompanhante_internacao'] == 0)):
        continue
    else:
        ano = df.at[i, 'ano_malaria']
        uf = df.at[i, 'uf']
        zona = df.at[i, 'zona']
        if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'dias_acompanhante_internacao']):
            dias = np.nanmedian(df['dias_acompanhante_internacao'][(df.internacao == 1)&(df.acompanhante_internacao == 1)])
        else:
            dias = df.at[i, 'dias_acompanhante_internacao']
        sexo = random.choice(['1','2'])
        remuneracao = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
        df.at[i, 'absenteeism_caregiver_expenditures'] = remuneracao*8*dias

df.drop(['internacao', 'acompanhante_internacao', 'dias_internacao','dias_acompanhante_internacao'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
df.head()

Intangible costs¶
The intangible costs in our model are those born out of the loss of quality of life associated with the episode. Our chief hypothesis is that this loss occurs only during the episode; we can't properly mensurate after-effects. The equation we use is:


expenditures = length of episode

 X (1 - QALY associated with episode)

 X daily wage


With daily wage coming from PNAD.











In [951]:



     


perda_qaly = float(os.environ['LOSS_QUALITY_LIFE'])



     















In [952]:



     


df['loss_quality_life_expenditures'] = 0

for i in df.index:
    ano = df.at[i, 'ano_malaria']
    uf = df.at[i, 'uf']
    sexo = df.at[i, 'sexo']
    zona = df.at[i, 'zona']
    if pd.isna(df.at[i, 'dias_malaria']):
        dias = np.nanmedian(df['dias_malaria'])
    else:
        dias = df.at[i, 'dias_malaria']
    remuneracao = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
    remuneracao = 8.8*remuneracao
    df.at[i, 'loss_quality_life_expenditures'] = perda_qaly*dias*remuneracao
df.drop(['dias_malaria'],axis = 1,inplace = True)
df.head()

Household burden dataset¶

Medicines, transports and patient absenteeism aggregation¶
For better visualization, it's also possible to aggregate the prevention methods, various medicines, means of transportation and patient activities absenteeism into single columns.











In [957]:



     


df_agg1 = df.copy()

df_agg1['medicine_expenditures'] = df_agg1[['medicine_expenditures', 'hospitalization_medicine_expenditures']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg1['direct_transport_expenditures'] = df_agg1[['direct_transport_expenditures_bus', 'direct_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle', 'direct_transport_expenditures_lift', 'direct_transport_expenditures_taxi', 'direct_transport_expenditures_uber', 'direct_transport_expenditures_lift', 'direct_transport_expenditures_boat']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg1['indirect_transport_expenditures'] = df_agg1[['indirect_transport_expenditures_by_foot', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_bus', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_lift', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_taxi', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_uber', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_lift', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_boat', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_sus']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg1['absenteeism_patient_expenditures'] = df_agg1[['absenteeism_main_work_expenditures','absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures','absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures','absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures', 'absenteeism_husbandry_expenditures', 'absenteeism_fishing_expenditures', 'absenteeism_extractivism_expenditures', 'absenteeism_mining_expenditures', 'absenteeism_commerce_expenditures', 'absenteeism_housework_expenditures']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg1.drop(['hospitalization_medicine_expenditures','direct_transport_expenditures_bus', 'direct_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle', 'direct_transport_expenditures_lift', 'direct_transport_expenditures_taxi', 'direct_transport_expenditures_uber', 'direct_transport_expenditures_lift', 'direct_transport_expenditures_boat', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_by_foot', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_bus', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_lift', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_taxi', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_uber', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_boat', 'indirect_transport_expenditures_sus', 'absenteeism_main_work_expenditures','absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures','absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures','absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures', 'absenteeism_husbandry_expenditures', 'absenteeism_fishing_expenditures', 'absenteeism_extractivism_expenditures', 'absenteeism_mining_expenditures', 'absenteeism_commerce_expenditures', 'absenteeism_housework_expenditures'], axis = 1, inplace = True)

Components aggregation¶
The expenditures can also be aggregated into components (direct, indirect and intangible).











In [959]:



     


df_agg2 = df_agg1.copy()

                         'loss_quality_life_expenditures': 'intangible_expenditures'},

Economic burden of Malaria in the Brazilian Amazon region¶
Using the items of cost calculated at household level in the field survey, we will next estimate the main purpose of the present work: the economic burden of Malaria in the Brazilian Amazon region. We will use the proportion of households that incurred into a given expenditure as well as its median value as an estimator of the true population expenditure.


First, we will apply some needed treatments at the datasets employed. THen, we will calculate the burden at municipality and State level.











Dataset treatment¶
The estimators are located in the 'df_full_stats' dataframe. To use it, we need to calculate the proportion of households that incurred into a given expenditure. This will be done by dividing the 'count' statistics by the number of households with recent Malaria (n = 1131).











In [966]:



     


columns = df_full_stats.columns.values.tolist()
columns.pop(0)
list = []
for column in columns:
    prop = df_full_stats.at[0,column]/1131
    list.append(prop)

list.insert(0,'prop')
df_full_stats.loc[len(df_full_stats)] = list
display(df_full_stats)

The dataframe 'df_mortality', that reunites data regarding prospective malaria-caused fatalities, has to be treated to conform itself to the codification of the other dataframes. Additionaly, we have to calculate the recover the starter age of the age groups.











In [971]:



     


df_mortality['uf'] = ""
df_mortality['idade'] = ""

for i in range(len(df_mortality)):
    if df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'AC':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '12'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'AM':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '13'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'AP':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '16'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'PA':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '15'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'RO':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '11'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'RR':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '14'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'TO':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '17'
    elif df_mortality.loc[i, 'UF'] == 'MT':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '51'
    else:
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'uf'] = '21'

    df_mortality.loc[i,'idade'] = df_mortality.loc[i, 'faixa_etaria'].split('-')[0]
    if df_mortality.loc[i, 'idade'] == '2':
        df_mortality.loc[i, 'idade'] = '1'

df_mortality.drop(['UF', 'faixa_etaria'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
df_mortality.head()

Burden by municipality¶
There will be two distinct methodologies employed here. For the prevention related expenditures, we will calculate the expenditure by municipality calculating a proportion of households that incurred in said expenditure. For the following expenditures, we will use the proportion of episodes that incurred in said expenditure. Also, every monetary value will be converted from 2019 BRL to 2024 PPP USD. To achieve this, we will declare a variable with the conversion factor.











In [973]:



     


ppp_usd = float(os.environ["PPP_USD_CONVERSION"])



     















Prevention burden¶
The estimation is:


expenditure = number of households in the municipality

 X proportion of households in field survey that incurred in said expenditure

 X median value of said expenditure in field survey











In [974]:



     


df2['prevention_expenditures'] = 0
for i in range(len(df2)):
    if df2.loc[i, 'class_IPA'] != 'Alto risco':
        continue
    else:
        df2.loc[i, 'prevention_expenditures'] = df2.loc[i, 'domicilios']*(df_full_stats['prevention_expenditures'][df_full_stats.stats == 'prop'].squeeze())*(df_full_stats['prevention_expenditures'][df_full_stats.stats == '50%'].squeeze())*ppp_usd
df2.drop(['class_IPA'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
df2.head()

Burden associated with other kinds of expenditures¶
In this subsection, we will calculate the other kinds of expenditures by the following formula:


expenditure = number of malaria episodes in the municipality

 X proportion of households in field survey that incurred in said expenditure

 X median value of said expenditure in field survey

Burden by State¶
The procedure established above will be followed throughly here, with an added section calculation the burden of premature mortality associated with malaria.











Prevention burden¶
The estimation is:


expenditure = number of households in the State

 X proportion of households in field survey that incurred in said expenditure

 X median value of said expenditure in field survey

Burden associated with premature mortality¶
To estimate the burden associated with premature mortality, we will consider the number of years lost by adopting IBGE estimates of conditional life expectancy. The years of lost income will then be evaluated against the average income, from PNAD. The formula is:


lost income = years of lost income due to malaria-related premature death

 X annual average wage











In [978]:



     


df_mortality = df_mortality.merge(df_life[['uf', 'idade', 'sexo', 'ex']], on = ['sexo', 'uf', 'idade'], how = 'left').merge(df_wage[['sexo', 'uf', 'mean']][df_wage.ano == '2019'], on = ['sexo', 'uf'], how = 'left')
df_mortality['renda_perdida'] = df_mortality['ex']*df_mortality['mean']*12*df_mortality['n']*ppp_usd
df_mortality.drop(['sexo', 'n', 'idade', 'ex', 'mean'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
df_mortality = df_mortality.groupby(['uf']).sum()
df_mortality.rename(columns = {'renda_perdida':'premature_mortality_burden'}, inplace = True)
df_mortality.head()

Exports¶
Finally, the results will be exported to a .xlsx file for futher analysis.











In [156]:



     


writer = pd.ExcelWriter(os.path.join(path_export, export_file), engine='xlsxwriter')

df2.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - full', index = False)
df_agg_municipality.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - items', index = False)
df_municipality_stats.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - stats', index = False)
df3.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - full', index = False)
df_agg_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - items', index = False)
df_state_stats.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - stats', index = False)

writer.close()



     















Sensitivity analysis¶
In this section, we will perform a sensisitivity analysis, first on prevention expenditures and then on absenteeism.











Prevention expenditures¶
Here, we will use the incidence data on the period 2015-9, instead of only 9. Any municipality that had high API in this timeframe will incur into prevention expenditures.

There are 51 municipalities that, at some point during 2015-9, had high incidence. So, as we did in the burder section, we stipulate that a percentage of households in these municipalites incurred into prevention expenditures.











In [177]:



     


for i in range(len(df2s)):
    if df2s.loc[i, 'municipality'] not in muns:
        continue
    else:
        df2s.loc[i, 'prevention_expenditures'] = df2s.loc[i, 'households']*(df_full_stats['prevention_expenditures'][df_full_stats.stats == 'prop'].squeeze())*(df_full_stats['prevention_expenditures'][df_full_stats.stats == '50%'].squeeze())*ppp_usd

df_agg_municipality_s = df2s.copy()

df_agg_municipality_s['direct_medical_expenditures'] = df2s[['exams_expenditures',
                                                   'appointmements_ambulatorial_expenditures', 'medicine_expenditures',
                                                   'hospitalization_medicine_expenditures']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg_municipality_s['direct_non_medical_expenditures'] = df2s[['food_lodging_expenditures',
                                                           'direct_transport_expenditures_bus',
                                                           'direct_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle',
                                                           'direct_transport_expenditures_lift',
                                                           'direct_transport_expenditures_taxi',
                                                           'direct_transport_expenditures_uber',
                                                           'direct_transport_expenditures_boat']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg_municipality_s['indirect_expenditures'] = df2s[['absenteeism_main_work_expenditures',
                                                       'absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures',
                                                       'absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures',
                                                       'absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures',

                                                       'indirect_transport_expenditures_lift',
                                                       'indirect_transport_expenditures_taxi',
                                                       'indirect_transport_expenditures_uber',
                                                       'indirect_transport_expenditures_boat',
                                                        'indirect_transport_expenditures_sus']].sum(axis = 1)
df_agg_municipality_s['direct_prevention_expenditures'] = df2s['prevention_expenditures']
df_agg_municipality_s['intangible_expenditures'] = df2s['loss_quality_life_expenditures']

Export¶
As we did above, we will export the results to a .xlsx file.











In [193]:



     


export_file_s = os.environ['EXPORT_SENSITIVITY_INCIDENCE']
writer = pd.ExcelWriter(os.path.join(path_export, export_file_s), engine='xlsxwriter')

df2s.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - full', index = False)
df_agg_municipality_s.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - items', index = False)
df_municipality_s_stats.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - stats', index = False)
df3s.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - full', index = False)
df_agg_state_s.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - items', index = False)
df_state_s_stats.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - stats', index = False)

writer.close()

Then we will calculate the expdentiures incurred due to absenteeism from main work, using the same procedures we did above:











In [989]:



     


def sensitivity_absenteeism(df, df_pnad, df_self, days, hours):
    absenteeism = []
    for i in df.index:
        if (df.at[i,'idade'] < 14) or ((df.at[i, 'trabalho_mal'] == '2') or (df.at[i, 'trabalho_mal'] == '3')):
            continue
        else:
            ano = df.at[i, 'ano_malaria']
            uf = df.at[i, 'uf']
            sexo = df.at[i, 'sexo']
            zona = df.at[i, 'zona']
            if df.at[i, 'tipo_trabalho_mal'] == '1':
                remuneracao = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
            elif df.at[i, 'tipo_trabalho_mal'] == '2':
                remuneracao = df_self.query(f"uf == '{uf}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
            else:
                remuneracao_sal = df_pnad.query(f"ano == '{ano}' & uf == '{uf}' & zona == '{zona}' & sexo == '{sexo}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
                remuneracao_self = df_self.query(f"uf == '{uf}'")['salario_hora'].squeeze()
                remuneracao = 0.5*(remuneracao_sal+remuneracao_self)
            if df.at[i, 'substituto_trab_mal'] == '1':
                remuneracao *= 2
            absenteeism.append(remuneracao*days*hours)           
    return np.nanmedian(absenteeism)



     















After defining the function, we will add a new column to the recently-created dataframe:











In [990]:



     


df_sens['absenteeism_main_work_expenditures'] = df_sens.apply(lambda x: sensitivity_absenteeism(df_n, df_pnad, df_self, x['days'], 8.5), axis = 1)

Finally, we wiil create a function to perform all the calculations established at the burden section in a single take:

def sensitivity_absenteeism_final(df2, df3, prop, expenditures, ppp_usd):
    df2['burden'] = 0
    df2['absenteeism_main_work_expenditures'] = 0
    df3['burden'] = 0
    df3.drop(['absenteeism_main_work_expenditures'], axis = 1, inplace = True)
    for i in df2.index:
        df2.loc[i, 'absenteeism_main_work_expenditures'] = df2.loc[i, 'episodes']*prop*expenditures*ppp_usd
    df2['burden'] = df2[['prevention_expenditures',
                        'exams_expenditures',
                               'appointmements_ambulatorial_expenditures', 'medicine_expenditures',
                               'hospitalization_medicine_expenditures', 'food_lodging_expenditures',
                               'direct_transport_expenditures_bus',
                               'direct_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle',
                               'direct_transport_expenditures_lift',
                               'direct_transport_expenditures_taxi',
                               'direct_transport_expenditures_uber',
                               'direct_transport_expenditures_boat',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_by_foot',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_bus',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_lift',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_taxi',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_uber',
                               'indirect_transport_expenditures_boat',
                                'indirect_transport_expenditures_sus',
                               'absenteeism_main_work_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_husbandry_expenditures',
                               'aabsenteeism_fishing_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_extractivism_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_mining_expenditures', 'absenteeism_commerce_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_housework_expenditures',
                               'absenteeism_caregiver_expenditures', 'loss_quality_life_expenditures']].sum(axis = 1)
    df2.fillna(0, inplace = True)
    exps = df2[['state', 'absenteeism_main_work_expenditures']].groupby('state').sum()
    df3 = df3.merge(exps, on = 'state', how = 'left')
    df3['burden'] = df3[['prevention_expenditures',
                    'exams_expenditures',
                           'appointmements_ambulatorial_expenditures', 'medicine_expenditures',
                           'hospitalization_medicine_expenditures', 'food_lodging_expenditures',

                           'indirect_transport_expenditures_taxi',
                           'indirect_transport_expenditures_uber',
                           'indirect_transport_expenditures_boat',
                            'indirect_transport_expenditures_sus',
                           'absenteeism_main_work_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_basic_school_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_tertiary_education_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_agriculture_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_husbandry_expenditures',
                           'aabsenteeism_fishing_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_extractivism_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_mining_expenditures', 'absenteeism_commerce_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_housework_expenditures',
                           'absenteeism_caregiver_expenditures', 'loss_quality_life_expenditures','premature_mortality_burden']].sum(axis = 1)

    df3.fillna(0, inplace = True)
    df_agg_municipality = df2.copy()

                                                       'appointmements_ambulatorial_expenditures', 'medicine_expenditures',
                                                       'hospitalization_medicine_expenditures']].sum(axis = 1)
    df_agg_municipality['direct_non_medical_expenditures'] = df2[['food_lodging_expenditures',
                                                               'direct_transport_expenditures_bus',
                                                               'direct_transport_expenditures_own_vehicle',
                                                               'direct_transport_expenditures_lift',
                                                               'direct_transport_expenditures_taxi',
                                                               'direct_transport_expenditures_uber',

Exports¶
As we've done throughout this notebook, the results of this section will be exported to a .xlsx filefor further analysis.











In [1004]:



     


export_file_a = os.environ['EXPORT_SENSITIVITY_ABSENTEEISM']
writer = pd.ExcelWriter(os.path.join(path_export, export_file_a), engine='xlsxwriter')

df10_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - full (Q10)', index = False)
df10_agg_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - items (Q10)', index = False)
df10_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - full (Q10)', index = False)
df10_agg_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - items (Q10)', index = False)
df20_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - full (Q20)', index = False)
df20_agg_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - items (Q20)', index = False)
df20_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - full (Q20)', index = False)
df20_agg_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - items (Q20)', index = False)
df40_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - full (Q40)', index = False)
df40_agg_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - items (Q40)', index = False)
df40_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - full (Q40)', index = False)
df40_agg_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - items (Q40)', index = False)
df50_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - full (Q50)', index = False)
df50_agg_mun.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - items (Q50)', index = False)
df50_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - full (Q50)', index = False)
df50_agg_state.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - items (Q50)', index = False)
df_mun_stats.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'Municipality - stats', index = False)
df_state_stats.to_excel(writer, sheet_name = 'State - stats', index = False)

writer.close()
